<ns2140:section xmlns:ns2140="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2se.jndi.introduction.introduction">
    
    <ns2141:title xmlns:ns2141="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Introduction to JNDI</ns2141:title>
    
    <ns2142:para xmlns:ns2142="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns2143:emphasis xmlns:ns2143="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Directories</ns2143:emphasis>, whether the common (and like-named) containers of files on your file system, or
        as higher-level, typically networked services, provide access to a variety of information
        about machines, networks, users, resources, applications, and so forth. It does so by arranging
        this information hierarchically, using unique <ns2144:emphasis xmlns:ns2144="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">names</ns2144:emphasis> for each piece of information. 
    </ns2142:para>
    <ns2145:para xmlns:ns2145="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        The Java Naming and Directory Interface (JNDI) API provides a unified interface to multiple naming and directory services. 
        As a standard part of the Java enterprise API set, JNDI enables seamless connectivity to heterogeneous enterprise 
        naming and directory services. Like most Java APIs, JNDI is composed of a standard set of of contracts (Interfaces) that
        enable the <ns2146:emphasis xmlns:ns2146="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">lookup</ns2146:emphasis>, <ns2147:emphasis xmlns:ns2147="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">binding</ns2147:emphasis>, <ns2148:emphasis xmlns:ns2148="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">searching</ns2148:emphasis>, <ns2149:emphasis xmlns:ns2149="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">navigation</ns2149:emphasis>
        and <ns2150:emphasis xmlns:ns2150="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">modification</ns2150:emphasis> of any number of different directory services, using a common toolset. These
        include:
        <ns2151:itemizedlist xmlns:ns2151="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            <ns2152:listitem xmlns:ns2152="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                <ns2153:para xmlns:ns2153="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Networked Java Objects (EJBs, RMI/CORBA Objects)</ns2153:para>
            </ns2152:listitem>
            <ns2154:listitem xmlns:ns2154="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                <ns2155:para xmlns:ns2155="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Resources, such as Pooled Database Connections, Printers and JavaMail Sessions</ns2155:para>
            </ns2154:listitem>
            <ns2156:listitem xmlns:ns2156="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                <ns2157:para xmlns:ns2157="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">LDAP Objects (including in Microsoft's ActiveDirectory)</ns2157:para>
            </ns2156:listitem>
            <ns2158:listitem xmlns:ns2158="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                <ns2159:para xmlns:ns2159="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">DNS (Domain Naming Service) to resolve host names</ns2159:para>
            </ns2158:listitem>
        </ns2151:itemizedlist>        
    </ns2145:para>
    <ns2160:para xmlns:ns2160="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        Simple and consistent access to these types of services are crucial to 
        complex, networked Java applications.
    </ns2160:para>
    
</ns2140:section>